intro: Daucus setifolius subsp. setifolius, commonly known as the slender-foliated carrot, is a member of the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its finely divided, feathery leaves and yellow flowers that bloom in umbels. The plant typically grows in dry, open habitats such as grasslands and rocky areas. Its roots are not as fleshy as those of the common carrot but are used in some traditional medicinal practices. It is native to regions of southern Europe and western Asia.
